main event: On May 23, 1957, a sighting of one white object, described as the size of a star or a dime at arm's length, was reported. The object appeared as a bright light and was observed in the air for approximately thirty minutes.
interesting points: The object was visually observed for a significant duration of thirty minutes.
The size of the object was compared to that of a star or the size of a dime at arm's length.
The report indicates that the object was seen as a bright light in the air.
No photographs of the object were included in the report.
The conclusion was categorized as possibly a balloon, insufficient data for evaluation, and other.
sighted object: one white object in the sky
